Document: class_openxrandroidthreadsettingsextension
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrandroidthreadsettingsextension.rst
Summary: Explains the importance of identifying application threads for XR performance and system scheduling adjustments.

For XR to be comfortable, it is important for applications to deliver frames quickly and consistently. In order to make sure the important application threads get their full share of time, these threads must be identified to the system, which will adjust their scheduling priority accordingly.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRAndroidThreadSettingsExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_openxrandroidthreadsettingsextension.rst
Summary: Defines thread type enumeration values and the method to set thread types for XR runtime scheduling priority adjustments.

Enumeration: ThreadType (int)
- THREAD_TYPE_APPLICATION_MAIN = 0: Hints to the XR runtime that the thread is doing time critical CPU tasks.
- THREAD_TYPE_APPLICATION_WORKER = 1: Hints to the XR runtime that the thread is doing background CPU tasks.
- THREAD_TYPE_RENDERER_MAIN = 2: Hints to the XR runtime that the thread is doing time critical graphics device tasks.
- THREAD_TYPE_RENDERER_WORKER = 3: Hints to the XR runtime that the thread is doing background graphics device tasks.

Method: set_application_thread_type(ThreadType thread_type, int thread_id = 0) → bool
Sets the thread type of the given thread, so that the XR runtime can adjust its scheduling priority accordingly. thread_id refers to the OS thread id (ie from gettid()). When thread_id is 0, it will set the thread type of the current thread. Note: The id returned by Thread.get_id() is incompatible with thread_id.